      • generateFor

        public final void generateFor(io.spine.tools.protoc.EntityState entityState,
                              io.spine.code.java.ClassName markAs)
        Configures strongly-typed fields generation for messages that represent an entity state.

        Example: 

         generateFor messages().entityState(), markAs("com.some.custom.Field")

        The statement above enables the strongly-typed fields generation for all messages that represent an entity state and marks the generated fields as some.custom.Field.

        It is expected by the Spine routines that the type passed to the markAs method is a public non-final descendant of EntityStateField and has a public constructor accepting a single Field argument.

      • generateFor

        public final void generateFor(PatternSelector pattern,
                              io.spine.code.java.ClassName markAs)
        Configures the strongly-typed fields generation for messages declared in files matching a given pattern.

        Example: 

         generateFor messages().inFiles(suffix: "messages.proto"), markAs("com.some.custom.Field")

        The statement above enables strongly-typed fields generation for all messages residing in files with names ending with messages.proto and marks the generated fields as some.custom.Field.

        It is expected by the Spine routines that the type passed to the markAs method is a public non-final descendant of SubscribableField and has a public constructor accepting a single Field argument.

        In case the field generation is configured for event and rejection messages, the passed field type should inherit from EventMessageField.

        The configuration may be applied multiple times to enable code generation for multiple file patterns.

      • generateFor

        public final void generateFor(java.lang.String type,
                              io.spine.code.java.ClassName markAs)
        Configures the strongly-typed fields generation for a message type with the passed name.

        Example: 

         generateFor "custom.message.Type", markAs("com.some.custom.Field")

        The statement above enables strongly-typed fields generation for the message type with Proto name custom.message.Type and marks the generated fields as some.custom.Field.

        It is expected by the Spine routines that the type passed to the markAs method is a public non-final descendant of SubscribableField and has a public constructor accepting a single Field argument.

        The configuration may be applied multiple times to enable code generation for multiple message types.
